20. A few questions your analysis can answer

These templates will help you answer:
	•	How much of the original population came back?
	•	Did returned accounts generally score higher or lower?
	•	Did the same accounts stay in the same risk band?
	•	Did max risk occur earlier or later in iteration 2?
	•	Did the score distribution tighten or widen?
	•	Which reviewed accounts disappeared entirely?
